Many tourism experts argue that the contribution of tourism to Nepal's national employment is much larger than what the numbers say. They point out that official statistics often leave out thousands of members of the informal tourism labour force: the daily-wage cook making breakfast at base camp, the young adult helping out in her family run tea-house after school, or the rickshaw-wala 
 dai enthusiastically showing tourists around Thamel.


#### A low barrier to entry 

Staying in the job market is difficult for idividuals with low educational attainment.  

And indeed, early results from our survey seem to support this hypothesis. Almost 80% of our respondents reported not having to sign any formal contract with their employers. 

